UI reports:
bq. No failed tests found, a possible compilation error occurred.

{noformat}
06-Apr-2011 07:51:23 	BUILD SUCCESSFUL
06-Apr-2011 07:51:23 	Total time: 20.24 seconds
06-Apr-2011 07:51:23 	Build process for 'CLI integration test - Confluece CLI - itest' returned with return code = 0
06-Apr-2011 07:51:23 	Parsing test results...
06-Apr-2011 07:51:23 	Failing build since test cases were expected but none were found.
{noformat}

However, there were *test results* even though none were successful. Since there were none failed, Bamboo should NOT fail the build.
{noformat}
<testsuite time='19.066' failures='0' errors='0' skipped='1' tests='1' name='confluencecli'>
{noformat}

Changed repo type from GIT -> SVN then tried executing a plan and got the following error;
{code}
Error encountered while triggering manual build: For input string: "e9f936fe8ae647bf59c414b649fb599fadaa1d72"

Plan 'TEST-TST' did not start{code}

Need to move the 
{code}
 finally
        {
            currentBuildResult.addBuildErrors(buildLogger.getStringErrorLogs());
        }
{code}
part from the tasks to task executor (or sth.)

Or make interceptor for each task that will only handle tasks' ownw errors

Given the following environment assignment:
{noformat}
MAVEN_OPTS=-Xmx512m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m -Xms128m
{noformat}
it will be actually passed as 
{noformat}
MAVEN_OPTS=-Xmx512m -XX:MaxPermSize
{noformat}
which will cause
{noformat}
24-Mar-2011 19:25:15 	Unrecognized VM option 'MaxPermSize'
24-Mar-2011 19:25:15 	Could not create the Java virtual machine.
{noformat}
